Sentencas: A transition layer between Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-delta (SDC) electrolyte and Sr0.8Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta (SCF0.8) nano cathode was introduced to improve electrochemical performances of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Enhanced performance of solid oxide fuel cells by introducing a transition layer between nanostructured cathode and electrolyte

Sentencas: A calcining - stripping method was used to introduce the transition layer on the SDC electrolyte.
Titulo: Enhanced performance of solid oxide fuel cells by introducing a transition layer between nanostructured cathode and electrolyte

Sentencas: Then a nano porous cathode was coated on the transition layer.
Titulo: Enhanced performance of solid oxide fuel cells by introducing a transition layer between nanostructured cathode and electrolyte

Sentencas: The microstructure of the nano cathode was optimized by adjusting its calcining temperature.
Titulo: Enhanced performance of solid oxide fuel cells by introducing a transition layer between nanostructured cathode and electrolyte

Sentencas: It was found that the transition layer played a vital role in improving the electrochemical performances of the nanostructured cathode by enhancing the interface connection between cathode and electrolyte.
Titulo: Enhanced performance of solid oxide fuel cells by introducing a transition layer between nanostructured cathode and electrolyte

Sentencas: Good electrochemical performance was obtained as the nano cathode calcined at 700 degrees C after introducing the transition layer.
Titulo: Enhanced performance of solid oxide fuel cells by introducing a transition layer between nanostructured cathode and electrolyte

Sentencas: The polarization resistance of the anode-supported SOFC at 700 degrees C was significantly reduced from 0.20 Omega cm(2) to 0.05 Omega cm(2), while the power density of the single cell was increased from 116 to 444 mW cm(-2).
Titulo: Enhanced performance of solid oxide fuel cells by introducing a transition layer between nanostructured cathode and electrolyte
